          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <!-- Section: Key Features -->
  <Section class:list={"bg-white"}>
    <Heading>
      <h2 slot="heading-title" class="font-black text-brand-green h2">Key Features</h2>
      <p slot="heading-content">
        Dive into stunning recreations of real-world landmarks, generated automatically by
        advanced voxelization. Explore cities, terrain, and even extraterrestrial data sets.
      </p>
    </Heading>

    <Grid>
      <div slot="grid-content-1">
        <div class="flex flex-col items-center prose text-center">
          <!-- Image container with fixed aspect ratio -->
          <div
            class="pixel-frame relative max-w-[520px] aspect-[13/14] not-prose w-full mx-auto mb-10"
            data-parallax-frame="true"
            data-parallax-speed="0.85"
            data-parallax-max="60"
          >
            <Picture
              src={Pizza}
              height={560}
              formats={["avif", "webp"]}
              alt="Voxel world illustration"
              loading="eager"
              fetchpriority="high"
              class="pixel-frame__image absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover z-[2]"
            />
            <Image
              src={PixelMask2}
              alt=""
              class="pixel-frame__overlay absolute inset-0 pointer-events-none select-none"
              loading="lazy"
              decoding="async"
              aria-hidden="true"
            />
          </div>
          <!-- Text below the image container -->
          <h3 class="h4 mt-0 font-black">Global 3D Tiles</h3>
          <p>
            We integrate with multiple public (and private) 3D Tiles data sources, including
            Google Earth and other open datasets. Roam entire cities or natural wonders without
            leaving your Minecraft client.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div slot="grid-content-2">
        <div class="flex flex-col items-center prose text-center">
          <!-- Image container with fixed aspect ratio -->
          <div
            class="pixel-frame relative max-w-[520px] aspect-[13/14] not-prose w-full mx-auto mb-10"
            data-parallax-frame="true"
            data-parallax-speed="1.35"
            data-parallax-max="85"
          >
            <Picture
              src={Spaghetti}
              height={560}
              formats={["avif", "webp"]}
              alt="Voxel world illustration"
              loading="eager"
              fetchpriority="high"
              class="pixel-frame__image absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover z-[2]"
            />
            <Image
              src={PixelMask1}
              alt=""
              class="pixel-frame__overlay absolute inset-0 pointer-events-none select-none"
              loading="lazy"
              decoding="async"
              aria-hidden="true"
            />
          </div>
          <h3 class="h4 mt-0 font-black">GPU-Powered</h3>
          <p>
            Our pipeline uses GPU-based voxelization for fast, on-demand chunk generation.
            Large photogrammetry data is handled quickly, ensuring minimal waiting time
            and high detail where it counts.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div slot="grid-content-3">
        <div class="flex flex-col items-center prose text-center">
          <!-- Image container with fixed aspect ratio -->
          <div
            class="pixel-frame relative max-w-[520px] aspect-[13/14] not-prose w-full mx-auto mb-10"
            data-parallax-frame="true"
            data-parallax-speed="1.85"
            data-parallax-max="110"
          >
            <Picture
              src={Fish}
              height={560}
              formats={["avif", "webp"]}
              alt="3D tile pipeline demonstration"
              loading="eager"
              fetchpriority="high"
              class="pixel-frame__image absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover z-[2]"
            />
            <Image
              src={PixelMask1}
              alt=""
              class="pixel-frame__overlay absolute inset-0 pointer-events-none select-none"
              loading="lazy"
              decoding="async"
              aria-hidden="true"
            />
          </div>
          <h3 class="h4 mt-0 font-black">Rich Textures</h3>
          <p>
            Each photogrammetry texture is transferred into Minecraft block coloration,
            giving you an immersive experience. Buildings, water, foliage&mdash;everything is
            mapped into the Minecraft palette.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </Grid>
  </Section>

  <!-- Section: Global 3D Tiles (Hero) -->
  <Section class:list={"bg-white"}>
    <Hero>
      <div slot="hero-content-left" class="prose lg:order-2">
        <h1 class="font-black">Global 3D Tiles in Action</h1>

        <p>
          Wondering how your city looks when turned into voxels? We load the highest resolution
          3D Tiles available, convert them to blocks, and stream them into Minecraft
          just like normal chunks. It's a seamless experience&mdash;just walk around, and the
          real-world data loads.
        </p>

        <p>
          We rely on a combination of open-source libraries and custom GPU code to
          handle the complexity of photorealistic data. This ensures a stable, visually
          appealing environment that captures the spirit of each real-world site.
        </p>

        <div class="mt-8">
          <Button url="/menu">
            <svg
